rComments: I feel so bad because I literally went to 0 classes but this class was so easy-going. It's a perfect elective bc it allowed me to focus on the required courses for my program. Joana is so nice and gives nice feedback. Very respectful of students!

Obviously she's great. She's taught this class countless times so she knows how it goes and how to teach it so it's easy to follow. Online due to COVID, and she was in Portugal at the time, so she was 5 hours ahead of us at all times but would answer emails even at 1am here (6am there) lol She's very kind and genuinely cares about her students

Joana is a really great prof to have! she explains the different dialects of Portuguese but focuses mainly on the Mainland Portuguese. There are a lot of assignments, but they are all easy to complete and allow for you to finish with a good grade. Final is a take home, definitely recommend her!
